      • willProcess

        boolean willProcess(JDBCcallFSMstate FSMstate,
                  java.lang.String executedObject,
                  java.lang.String executedMethod,
                  java.lang.Object[] executedParameter,
                  java.lang.String callBack)
        Informs if current context is valid for processing any transition Note that this method does not inform about next state
        Parameters:
        FSMstate - Object keeping state machine's state
        executedObject - Name of intercepted object
        executedMethod - Name of interepted method
        executedParameter - Array of intercepted arguments
        callBack - Name of a interception function: preInvokeCallback, postInvokeCallback, postInvokeExceptionCallback
        Returns:
        True/false indication if any transition may be processed

      • process

        JDBCcallFSM process(JDBCcallFSMstate FSMstate,
                  java.lang.String executedObject,
                  java.lang.String executedMethod,
                  java.lang.Object[] executedParameter,
                  java.lang.String callBack)
        Process transition logic and return next state. Note that transition logic belongs to current state. Logic to handle entering EXECUTED state must be handled in previous state: PREPARED, CONFIGURED [PREPARED---logic--->] [EXECUTED] [CONFIGURED---logic--->] [EXECUTED]
        Parameters:
        FSMstate - Object keeping state machine's state
        executedObject - Name of intercepted object
        executedMethod - Name of interepted method
        executedParameter - Array of intercepted arguments
        callBack - Name of a interception function: preInvokeCallback, postInvokeCallback, postInvokeExceptionCallback
        Returns:
        Next state, after execution of transition logic
